20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-search-antitrust-monopoly-doj-ruling-decision-chrome-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20will%20be%20barred%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20entering%20exclusive%20contracts%20with%20partners%20such%20as%20Apple%20to%20give%20its%20search%20engine%20pride%20of%20place.%20It%20will%20also%20be%20forced%20to%20share%20some%20search%20data%20with%20rivals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20won't%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-sell-chrome-search-winners-losers-doj-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eforced%20to%20spin%20off%20Chrome%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20remedy%20that%20was%20previously%20on%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20opens%20up%20a%20host%20of%20opportunities%20for%20Google's%20AI%20rivals%2C%20from%20OpenAI%20and%20Perplexity%20to%20its%20long-standing%20search%20challenger%2C%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20previously%20said%20it%20intends%20to%20appeal%20the%20ruling%2C%20and%20the%20case%20will%20likely%20drag%20on%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20concerns%20about%20how%20these%20requirements%20will%20impact%20our%20users%20and%20their%20privacy%2C%20and%20we're%20reviewing%20the%20decision%20closely%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lee-Anne%20Mulholland%2C%20Google's%20vice%20president%20of%20regulatory%20affairs%2C%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20winners%20and%20losers%20based%20on%20the%20penalties%20that%20were%20handed%20out%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222522c9d8-39d2-4557-9a38-9e2fd9c3eaa5%5C%22%3EWinners%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f11c5ae-bc5a-417d-8b08-e8a7a0d02173%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETuesday's%20ruling%20arguably%20hands%20Google%20the%20best-case%20scenario.%20For%20one%2C%20it%20will%20not%20be%20forced%20to%20sell%20off%20its%20Chrome%20browser%2C%20which%20is%20a%20huge%20distribution%20tool%20for%20funneling%20users%20to%20Google%20Search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20does%20Chrome%20capture%20those%20all-important%20search%20queries%20for%20Google%2C%20it%20also%20captures%20user%20query%20data%20that%20it%20can%20use%20to%20make%20Google%20Search%20even%20better.%20In%20short%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20a%20painful%20loss%20for%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Mehta%20ruled%2C%20however%2C%20that%20Google%20will%20be%20barred%20from%20entering%20exclusive%20agreements%20to%20distribute%20its%20search%20engine%2C%20though%20he%20stopped%20short%20of%20blocking%20those%20payments%20altogether.%20The%20ruling%20did%20block%20Google%20from%20entering%20deals%20that%20force%20partners%20to%20install%20apps%20such%20as%20Search%20or%20Chrome%20for%20access%20to%20the%20Google%20Play%20store.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20payments%20to%20Apple%20and%20other%20partners%20to%20secure%20its%20search%20engine%20in%20a%20default%20position%20have%20been%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20DOJ%20case%20from%20the%20very%20start.%20The%20decision%20on%20Tuesday%20will%20allow%20Google%20to%20keep%20paying%20for%20that%20default%20placement%20with%20Apple%20and%20other%20partners%20%E2%80%94%20it%20just%20won't%20be%20allowed%20to%20force%20them%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3Euse%20only%3C%2Fem%3E%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2294dcbe9e-56d2-40c9-a9dc-6ce613ffa1ee%5C%22%3EApple%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-apple-iphone-search-engine-safari-deal-20-billion-2022-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20Apple%20around%20%2420%20billion%20in%202022%20to%20be%20the%20default%20search%20engine%20on%20the%20iPhone.%20That's%20about%20a%20fifth%20of%20Apple's%20annual%20services%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20that%20Google%20can%20continue%20making%20those%20payments%20%E2%80%94%20so%20long%20as%20they%20are%20not%20exclusive%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20win%20for%20Apple%2C%20which%20can%20continue%20to%20collect%20its%20fee%20from%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20partnership%20has%20been%20mutually%20beneficial.%20In%202020%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-antitrust-apple-search-payments-iphone-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20internally%20projected%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20would%20lose%20between%2060%25%20and%2080%25%20of%20its%20search%20volume%20on%20Apple%20devices%20if%20it%20were%20replaced%20as%20the%20default%20general%20search%20engine%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-antitrust-doj-ruling-monopoly-search-apple-iphone-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20court%20filing%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year.%20That%20figure%20would%20represent%20between%20%2428.2%20billion%20and%20%2432.7%20billion%20in%20net%20revenue%20losses%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20agreement%20between%20Google%20and%20Apple%20still%20allowed%2C%20it%20could%20also%20open%20the%20door%20to%20more%20collaboration%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20now%20see%20a%20green%20light%20for%20a%20bigger%20Gemini%20AI%20partnership%20between%20Apple%20and%20Google%20with%20this%20DOJ%20case%20now%20in%20the%20rear%20view%20mirror%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Wedbush%20Securities%20analyst%20Dan%20Ives%20in%20a%20note%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f62e0c39-dedf-47c7-8e76-8dee7c5b161c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOpenAI%20and%20Perplexity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20Google%20can't%20prohibit%20Apple%20from%20including%20other%20search%20tools%20on%20the%20iPhone%2C%20its%20AI%20rivals%20OpenAI%20and%20Perplexity%20could%20benefit%20substantially.%20OpenAI%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-steps-up-google-challenge-launches-chatgpt-search-tool-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaunched%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20own%20search%20service%20in%202024%2C%20and%20one%20of%20its%20biggest%20challenge